<GUIClass name="CMUI_SliderHandle" id="4abf0757-8237-4723-b8e7-31b9bc9f703d">
    <superclass name="CMUI_MoveableFrame"/>
    <transient/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>

This control is expected to be placed inside a parent frame. This frame can then have colours, drawings, picture and other controls to get the preferred look.

The control takes the dimensions of the parent and sets its min and max X value.

As the mouse is moved the LEFT value is changed and appears to move.

The parent can be any size and the number of pixels used for the width is used to determine a pixels per percentage of the width. This is to allow the width of the parent to represent a percentage value of 1 to 100.

The percentage value is stored in valuePC.

The slider can also be given a min and max amount value that you want to it to use as the amounts say 400 to 600 or 0.5 to 1.5.

SO if your app wants a simple percentage then use the valuePC, else set the start and end values and the control will return a value.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="_usergui"/>
